            SLCE Updates for Fall 2022
          Heading link



 
Copy link



Currently Student Leadership and Civic Engagement are on adjusted summer hours. Please email slce@uic.edu to contact members of our team, and to schedule in person or virtual meetings as needed.
Looking to get involved with SLCE this fall semester? Visit here for all relevant links, or see below for upcoming dates and deadlines for the start of the fall semester:
Fall Day of Service – Friday, August 26, 2022.  Visit go.uic.edu/FallDayOfService to register
Make Mondays Matter – Typically the first Monday of each month, planned to be on-campus and in-person.  The first one of the fall semester will be Monday, September 12th. Sign up starting August 22nd at service.uic.edu
Get Involved with Volunteer Experiences (GIVE) – Second Saturday of each month, planned to be off-campus and in-person.  The first one of the fall semester will be Saturday, September 10th.  Sign up starting August 22nd at service.uic.edu
Service Roundtable Meetings – Third Thursday of each month, virtual, starting in September – visit slce.uic.edu/service/service-focused-student-organizations to learn more
Ignite Leadership Experience – Will begin the week of September 19th and run weekly for 6 weeks until the last full week in October. Applications will open Monday, August 1, 2022.  The deadline to apply is Wednesday, September 7, 2022.
Leadership Book Club – Starting Wednesday, September 28th and will meet every 2 weeks virtually.  Sign ups will start Monday August 22nd – Visit go.uic.edu/bookclub
Flashpoint Leadership/Certified Peer Educator Training – This one day training will take place the end of September.  More information coming soon.
Leadership Workshop series – One session per month – Virtual with more information coming soon.  Check out past workshops at slce.uic.edu/leadership/workshops
Civic Engagement Workshop series – One session per month – Virtual with varying topics: more information coming soon!


      Sign Up to receive the SLCE Newsletter!
    










